{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"You all know the truth of what I'm going to say."},{"time":3000,"text":"I think the intuition that inequality is divisive and socially corrosive"},{"time":7000,"text":"has been around since before the French Revolution."},{"time":11000,"text":"What's changed"},{"time":13000,"text":"is we now can look at the evidence,"},{"time":15000,"text":"we can compare societies, more and less equal societies,"},{"time":18000,"text":"and see what inequality does."},{"time":21000,"text":"I'm going to take you through that data"},{"time":24000,"text":"and then explain why"},{"time":26000,"text":"the links I'm going to be showing you exist."}]},{"cues":[{"time":30000,"text":"But first, see what a miserable lot we are."},{"time":33000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":35000,"text":"I want to start though"},{"time":37000,"text":"with a paradox."},{"time":40000,"text":"This shows you life expectancy"},{"time":42000,"text":"against gross national income --"},{"time":44000,"text":"how rich countries are on average."},{"time":46000,"text":"And you see the countries on the right,"},{"time":48000,"text":"like Norway and the USA,"},{"time":50000,"text":"are twice as rich as Israel, Greece, Portugal on the left."},{"time":55000,"text":"And it makes no difference to their life expectancy at all."},{"time":59000,"text":"There's no suggestion of a relationship there."},{"time":61000,"text":"But if we look within our societies,"},{"time":64000,"text":"there are extraordinary social gradients in health"},{"time":67000,"text":"running right across society."},{"time":69000,"text":"This, again, is life expectancy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":71000,"text":"These are small areas of England and Wales --"},{"time":73000,"text":"the poorest on the right, the richest on the left."},{"time":77000,"text":"A lot of difference between the poor and the rest of us."},{"time":80000,"text":"Even the people just below the top"},{"time":82000,"text":"have less good health"},{"time":84000,"text":"than the people at the top."},{"time":86000,"text":"So income means something very important"},{"time":88000,"text":"within our societies,"},{"time":90000,"text":"and nothing between them."},{"time":93000,"text":"The explanation of that paradox"},{"time":96000,"text":"is that, within our societies,"},{"time":98000,"text":"we're looking at relative income"},{"time":100000,"text":"or social position, social status --"},{"time":103000,"text":"where we are in relation to each other"},{"time":106000,"text":"and the size of the gaps between us."},{"time":109000,"text":"And as soon as you've got that idea,"},{"time":111000,"text":"you should immediately wonder:"},{"time":113000,"text":"what happens if we widen the differences,"},{"time":116000,"text":"or compress them,"},{"time":118000,"text":"make the income differences bigger or smaller?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":120000,"text":"And that's what I'm going to show you."},{"time":123000,"text":"I'm not using any hypothetical data."},{"time":125000,"text":"I'm taking data from the U.N. --"},{"time":127000,"text":"it's the same as the World Bank has --"},{"time":129000,"text":"on the scale of income differences"},{"time":131000,"text":"in these rich developed market democracies."},{"time":134000,"text":"The measure we've used,"},{"time":136000,"text":"because it's easy to understand and you can download it,"},{"time":138000,"text":"is how much richer the top 20 percent"},{"time":140000,"text":"than the bottom 20 percent in each country."},{"time":143000,"text":"And you see in the more equal countries on the left --"},{"time":146000,"text":"Japan, Finland, Norway, Sweden --"},{"time":148000,"text":"the top 20 percent are about three and a half, four times as rich"},{"time":150000,"text":"as the bottom 20 percent."},{"time":153000,"text":"But on the more unequal end --"},{"time":155000,"text":"U.K., Portugal, USA, Singapore --"},{"time":157000,"text":"the differences are twice as big."},{"time":160000,"text":"On that measure, we are twice as unequal"},{"time":163000,"text":"as some of the other successful market democracies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":167000,"text":"Now I'm going to show you what that does to our societies."},{"time":171000,"text":"We collected data on problems with social gradients,"},{"time":174000,"text":"the kind of problems that are more common"},{"time":176000,"text":"at the bottom of the social ladder."},{"time":178000,"text":"Internationally comparable data on life expectancy,"},{"time":181000,"text":"on kids' maths and literacy scores,"},{"time":184000,"text":"on infant mortality rates, homicide rates,"},{"time":187000,"text":"proportion of the population in prison, teenage birthrates,"},{"time":190000,"text":"levels of trust,"},{"time":192000,"text":"obesity, mental illness --"},{"time":194000,"text":"which in standard diagnostic classification"},{"time":197000,"text":"includes drug and alcohol addiction --"},{"time":199000,"text":"and social mobility."},{"time":201000,"text":"We put them all in one index."},{"time":204000,"text":"They're all weighted equally."},{"time":206000,"text":"Where a country is is a sort of average score on these things."},{"time":209000,"text":"And there, you see it"},{"time":211000,"text":"in relation to the measure of inequality I've just shown you,"},{"time":214000,"text":"which I shall use over and over again in the data."},{"time":217000,"text":"The more unequal countries"},{"time":219000,"text":"are doing worse"},{"time":221000,"text":"on all these kinds of social problems."},{"time":223000,"text":"It's an extraordinarily close correlation."},{"time":226000,"text":"But if you look at that same index"},{"time":228000,"text":"of health and social problems"},{"time":230000,"text":"in relation to GNP per capita,"},{"time":232000,"text":"gross national income,"},{"time":234000,"text":"there's nothing there,"},{"time":236000,"text":"no correlation anymore."}]},{"cues":[{"time":239000,"text":"We were a little bit worried"},{"time":241000,"text":"that people might think"},{"time":243000,"text":"we'd been choosing problems to suit our argument"},{"time":245000,"text":"and just manufactured this evidence,"},{"time":248000,"text":"so we also did a paper in the British Medical Journal"},{"time":251000,"text":"on the UNICEF index of child well-being."},{"time":255000,"text":"It has 40 different components"},{"time":257000,"text":"put together by other people."},{"time":259000,"text":"It contains whether kids can talk to their parents,"},{"time":262000,"text":"whether they have books at home,"},{"time":264000,"text":"what immunization rates are like, whether there's bullying at school."},{"time":267000,"text":"Everything goes into it."},{"time":269000,"text":"Here it is in relation to that same measure of inequality."},{"time":273000,"text":"Kids do worse in the more unequal societies."},{"time":276000,"text":"Highly significant relationship."},{"time":279000,"text":"But once again,"},{"time":281000,"text":"if you look at that measure of child well-being,"},{"time":284000,"text":"in relation to national income per person,"},{"time":286000,"text":"there's no relationship,"},{"time":288000,"text":"no suggestion of a relationship."}]},{"cues":[{"time":291000,"text":"What all the data I've shown you so far says"},{"time":294000,"text":"is the same thing."},{"time":296000,"text":"The average well-being of our societies"},{"time":298000,"text":"is not dependent any longer"},{"time":301000,"text":"on national income and economic growth."},{"time":304000,"text":"That's very important in poorer countries,"},{"time":306000,"text":"but not in the rich developed world."},{"time":309000,"text":"But the differences between us"},{"time":311000,"text":"and where we are in relation to each other"},{"time":313000,"text":"now matter very much."},{"time":316000,"text":"I'm going to show you some of the separate bits of our index."},{"time":319000,"text":"Here, for instance, is trust."},{"time":321000,"text":"It's simply the proportion of the population"},{"time":323000,"text":"who agree most people can be trusted."},{"time":325000,"text":"It comes from the World Values Survey."},{"time":327000,"text":"You see, at the more unequal end,"},{"time":329000,"text":"it's about 15 percent of the population"},{"time":332000,"text":"who feel they can trust others."},{"time":334000,"text":"But in the more equal societies,"},{"time":336000,"text":"it rises to 60 or 65 percent."},{"time":340000,"text":"And if you look at measures of involvement in community life"},{"time":343000,"text":"or social capital,"},{"time":345000,"text":"very similar relationships"},{"time":347000,"text":"closely related to inequality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":350000,"text":"I may say, we did all this work twice."},{"time":353000,"text":"We did it first on these rich, developed countries,"},{"time":356000,"text":"and then as a separate test bed,"},{"time":358000,"text":"we repeated it all on the 50 American states --"},{"time":361000,"text":"asking just the same question:"},{"time":363000,"text":"do the more unequal states"},{"time":365000,"text":"do worse on all these kinds of measures?"},{"time":367000,"text":"So here is trust from a general social survey of the federal government"},{"time":371000,"text":"related to inequality."},{"time":373000,"text":"Very similar scatter"},{"time":375000,"text":"over a similar range of levels of trust."},{"time":377000,"text":"Same thing is going on."},{"time":379000,"text":"Basically we found"},{"time":381000,"text":"that almost anything that's related to trust internationally"},{"time":384000,"text":"is related to trust amongst the 50 states"},{"time":386000,"text":"in that separate test bed."},{"time":388000,"text":"We're not just talking about a fluke."}]},{"cues":[{"time":390000,"text":"This is mental illness."},{"time":392000,"text":"WHO put together figures"},{"time":394000,"text":"using the same diagnostic interviews"},{"time":396000,"text":"on random samples of the population"},{"time":398000,"text":"to allow us to compare rates of mental illness"},{"time":401000,"text":"in each society."},{"time":403000,"text":"This is the percent of the population"},{"time":405000,"text":"with any mental illness in the preceding year."},{"time":408000,"text":"And it goes from about eight percent"},{"time":411000,"text":"up to three times that --"},{"time":413000,"text":"whole societies"},{"time":415000,"text":"with three times the level of mental illness of others."},{"time":418000,"text":"And again, closely related to inequality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":422000,"text":"This is violence."},{"time":424000,"text":"These red dots are American states,"},{"time":426000,"text":"and the blue triangles are Canadian provinces."},{"time":430000,"text":"But look at the scale of the differences."},{"time":433000,"text":"It goes from 15 homicides per million"},{"time":436000,"text":"up to 150."},{"time":439000,"text":"This is the proportion of the population in prison."},{"time":442000,"text":"There's a about a tenfold difference there,"},{"time":445000,"text":"log scale up the side."},{"time":447000,"text":"But it goes from about 40 to 400"},{"time":449000,"text":"people in prison."},{"time":452000,"text":"That relationship"},{"time":454000,"text":"is not mainly driven by more crime."},{"time":456000,"text":"In some places, that's part of it."},{"time":459000,"text":"But most of it is about more punitive sentencing,"},{"time":461000,"text":"harsher sentencing."},{"time":463000,"text":"And the more unequal societies"},{"time":465000,"text":"are more likely also to retain the death penalty."},{"time":469000,"text":"Here we have children dropping out of high school."},{"time":474000,"text":"Again, quite big differences."},{"time":476000,"text":"Extraordinarily damaging,"},{"time":478000,"text":"if you're talking about using the talents of the population."}]},{"cues":[{"time":481000,"text":"This is social mobility."},{"time":484000,"text":"It's actually a measure of mobility"},{"time":486000,"text":"based on income."},{"time":488000,"text":"Basically, it's asking:"},{"time":490000,"text":"do rich fathers have rich sons"},{"time":492000,"text":"and poor fathers have poor sons,"},{"time":494000,"text":"or is there no relationship between the two?"},{"time":497000,"text":"And at the more unequal end,"},{"time":499000,"text":"fathers' income is much more important --"},{"time":502000,"text":"in the U.K., USA."},{"time":505000,"text":"And in Scandinavian countries,"},{"time":507000,"text":"fathers' income is much less important."},{"time":509000,"text":"There's more social mobility."},{"time":512000,"text":"And as we like to say --"},{"time":514000,"text":"and I know there are a lot of Americans in the audience here --"},{"time":517000,"text":"if Americans want to live the American dream,"},{"time":520000,"text":"they should go to Denmark."}]},{"cues":[{"time":522000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":524000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":528000,"text":"I've shown you just a few things in italics here."},{"time":531000,"text":"I could have shown a number of other problems."},{"time":533000,"text":"They're all problems that tend to be more common"},{"time":535000,"text":"at the bottom of the social gradient."},{"time":537000,"text":"But there are endless problems with social gradients"},{"time":542000,"text":"that are worse in more unequal countries --"},{"time":544000,"text":"not just a little bit worse,"},{"time":546000,"text":"but anything from twice as common to 10 times as common."},{"time":549000,"text":"Think of the expense,"},{"time":551000,"text":"the human cost of that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":554000,"text":"I want to go back though to this graph that I showed you earlier"},{"time":556000,"text":"where we put it all together"},{"time":558000,"text":"to make two points."},{"time":560000,"text":"One is that, in graph after graph,"},{"time":563000,"text":"we find the countries that do worse,"},{"time":565000,"text":"whatever the outcome,"},{"time":567000,"text":"seem to be the more unequal ones,"},{"time":569000,"text":"and the ones that do well"},{"time":571000,"text":"seem to be the Nordic countries and Japan."},{"time":574000,"text":"So what we're looking at"},{"time":576000,"text":"is general social disfunction related to inequality."},{"time":579000,"text":"It's not just one or two things that go wrong,"},{"time":581000,"text":"it's most things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":583000,"text":"The other really important point I want to make on this graph"},{"time":586000,"text":"is that, if you look at the bottom,"},{"time":588000,"text":"Sweden and Japan,"},{"time":591000,"text":"they're very different countries in all sorts of ways."},{"time":594000,"text":"The position of women,"},{"time":596000,"text":"how closely they keep to the nuclear family,"},{"time":598000,"text":"are on opposite ends of the poles"},{"time":600000,"text":"in terms of the rich developed world."},{"time":602000,"text":"But another really important difference"},{"time":604000,"text":"is how they get their greater equality."},{"time":607000,"text":"Sweden has huge differences in earnings,"},{"time":610000,"text":"and it narrows the gap through taxation,"},{"time":612000,"text":"general welfare state,"},{"time":614000,"text":"generous benefits and so on."},{"time":617000,"text":"Japan is rather different though."},{"time":619000,"text":"It starts off with much smaller differences in earnings before tax."},{"time":622000,"text":"It has lower taxes."},{"time":624000,"text":"It has a smaller welfare state."},{"time":626000,"text":"And in our analysis of the American states,"},{"time":628000,"text":"we find rather the same contrast."},{"time":630000,"text":"There are some states that do well through redistribution,"},{"time":633000,"text":"some states that do well"},{"time":635000,"text":"because they have smaller income differences before tax."},{"time":638000,"text":"So we conclude"},{"time":640000,"text":"that it doesn't much matter how you get your greater equality,"},{"time":643000,"text":"as long as you get there somehow."}]},{"cues":[{"time":645000,"text":"I am not talking about perfect equality,"},{"time":647000,"text":"I'm talking about what exists in rich developed market democracies."},{"time":653000,"text":"Another really surprising part of this picture"},{"time":658000,"text":"is that it's not just the poor"},{"time":660000,"text":"who are affected by inequality."},{"time":663000,"text":"There seems to be some truth in John Donne's"},{"time":665000,"text":"\"No man is an island.\""},{"time":668000,"text":"And in a number of studies, it's possible to compare"},{"time":671000,"text":"how people do in more and less equal countries"},{"time":674000,"text":"at each level in the social hierarchy."},{"time":677000,"text":"This is just one example."},{"time":680000,"text":"It's infant mortality."},{"time":682000,"text":"Some Swedes very kindly classified a lot of their infant deaths"},{"time":685000,"text":"according to the British register of general socioeconomic classification."},{"time":690000,"text":"And so it's anachronistically"},{"time":693000,"text":"a classification by fathers' occupations,"},{"time":695000,"text":"so single parents go on their own."},{"time":697000,"text":"But then where it says \"low social class,\""},{"time":700000,"text":"that's unskilled manual occupations."},{"time":703000,"text":"It goes through towards the skilled manual occupations in the middle,"},{"time":707000,"text":"then the junior non-manual,"},{"time":709000,"text":"going up high to the professional occupations --"},{"time":712000,"text":"doctors, lawyers,"},{"time":714000,"text":"directors of larger companies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":716000,"text":"You see there that Sweden does better than Britain"},{"time":719000,"text":"all the way across the social hierarchy."},{"time":724000,"text":"The biggest differences are at the bottom of society."},{"time":726000,"text":"But even at the top,"},{"time":728000,"text":"there seems to be a small benefit"},{"time":730000,"text":"to being in a more equal society."},{"time":732000,"text":"We show that on about five different sets of data"},{"time":735000,"text":"covering educational outcomes"},{"time":737000,"text":"and health in the United States and internationally."},{"time":740000,"text":"And that seems to be the general picture --"},{"time":743000,"text":"that greater equality makes most difference at the bottom,"},{"time":746000,"text":"but has some benefits even at the top."}]},{"cues":[{"time":749000,"text":"But I should say a few words about what's going on."},{"time":753000,"text":"I think I'm looking and talking"},{"time":755000,"text":"about the psychosocial effects of inequality."},{"time":758000,"text":"More to do with feelings of superiority and inferiority,"},{"time":761000,"text":"of being valued and devalued,"},{"time":763000,"text":"respected and disrespected."},{"time":766000,"text":"And of course, those feelings"},{"time":768000,"text":"of the status competition that comes out of that"},{"time":771000,"text":"drives the consumerism in our society."},{"time":774000,"text":"It also leads to status insecurity."},{"time":777000,"text":"We worry more about how we're judged and seen by others,"},{"time":781000,"text":"whether we're regarded as attractive, clever,"},{"time":784000,"text":"all that kind of thing."},{"time":787000,"text":"The social-evaluative judgments increase,"},{"time":790000,"text":"the fear of those social-evaluative judgments."}]},{"cues":[{"time":794000,"text":"Interestingly,"},{"time":796000,"text":"some parallel work going on in social psychology:"},{"time":800000,"text":"some people reviewed 208 different studies"},{"time":803000,"text":"in which volunteers had been invited"},{"time":806000,"text":"into a psychological laboratory"},{"time":808000,"text":"and had their stress hormones,"},{"time":810000,"text":"their responses to doing stressful tasks, measured."},{"time":814000,"text":"And in the review,"},{"time":816000,"text":"what they were interested in seeing"},{"time":818000,"text":"is what kind of stresses"},{"time":820000,"text":"most reliably raise levels of cortisol,"},{"time":823000,"text":"the central stress hormone."},{"time":825000,"text":"And the conclusion was"},{"time":827000,"text":"it was tasks that included social-evaluative threat --"},{"time":830000,"text":"threats to self-esteem or social status"},{"time":833000,"text":"in which others can negatively judge your performance."},{"time":836000,"text":"Those kind of stresses"},{"time":838000,"text":"have a very particular effect"},{"time":841000,"text":"on the physiology of stress."}]},{"cues":[{"time":845000,"text":"Now we have been criticized."},{"time":847000,"text":"Of course, there are people who dislike this stuff"},{"time":850000,"text":"and people who find it very surprising."},{"time":853000,"text":"I should tell you though"},{"time":855000,"text":"that when people criticize us for picking and choosing data,"},{"time":858000,"text":"we never pick and choose data."},{"time":860000,"text":"We have an absolute rule"},{"time":862000,"text":"that if our data source has data for one of the countries we're looking at,"},{"time":865000,"text":"it goes into the analysis."},{"time":867000,"text":"Our data source decides"},{"time":869000,"text":"whether it's reliable data,"},{"time":871000,"text":"we don't."},{"time":873000,"text":"Otherwise that would introduce bias."}]},{"cues":[{"time":875000,"text":"What about other countries?"},{"time":877000,"text":"There are 200 studies"},{"time":880000,"text":"of health in relation to income and equality"},{"time":883000,"text":"in the academic peer-reviewed journals."},{"time":886000,"text":"This isn't confined to these countries here,"},{"time":889000,"text":"hiding a very simple demonstration."},{"time":891000,"text":"The same countries,"},{"time":893000,"text":"the same measure of inequality,"},{"time":895000,"text":"one problem after another."},{"time":899000,"text":"Why don't we control for other factors?"},{"time":901000,"text":"Well we've shown you that GNP per capita"},{"time":903000,"text":"doesn't make any difference."},{"time":905000,"text":"And of course, others using more sophisticated methods in the literature"},{"time":909000,"text":"have controlled for poverty and education"},{"time":911000,"text":"and so on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":915000,"text":"What about causality?"},{"time":917000,"text":"Correlation in itself doesn't prove causality."},{"time":920000,"text":"We spend a good bit of time."},{"time":922000,"text":"And indeed, people know the causal links quite well"},{"time":924000,"text":"in some of these outcomes."},{"time":926000,"text":"The big change in our understanding"},{"time":928000,"text":"of drivers of chronic health"},{"time":930000,"text":"in the rich developed world"},{"time":932000,"text":"is how important chronic stress from social sources"},{"time":936000,"text":"is affecting the immune system,"},{"time":938000,"text":"the cardiovascular system."},{"time":941000,"text":"Or for instance, the reason why violence"},{"time":943000,"text":"becomes more common in more unequal societies"},{"time":946000,"text":"is because people are sensitive to being looked down on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":951000,"text":"I should say that to deal with this,"},{"time":954000,"text":"we've got to deal with the post-tax things"},{"time":956000,"text":"and the pre-tax things."},{"time":958000,"text":"We've got to constrain income,"},{"time":961000,"text":"the bonus culture incomes at the top."},{"time":963000,"text":"I think we must make our bosses accountable to their employees"},{"time":966000,"text":"in any way we can."},{"time":969000,"text":"I think the take-home message though"},{"time":972000,"text":"is that we can improve the real quality of human life"},{"time":976000,"text":"by reducing the differences in incomes between us."},{"time":979000,"text":"Suddenly we have a handle"},{"time":981000,"text":"on the psychosocial well-being of whole societies,"},{"time":983000,"text":"and that's exciting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":985000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":987000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}